Conclusion¶

The analysis of the data reveals that Germany generates the highest revenue, while the United States generates the least. Germany stands out as the country with the largest revenue compared to any other country, while France, the United Kingdom, and the United States do not show any significant differences in the revenue generated. Bike accessories are the most popular category in all countries, with the largest number of sales, but the types of products sold vary among the countries. Germany generates the highest margins, while France, the United Kingdom, and the United States have negative margins in the bike category. There is an 11-year difference in the ages of customers among the countries, with 41-year-old customers frequenting German locations the most and 30-year-old customers being more prevalent in France.

However, the current multinational strategy of selling the exact same products in all four countries is not proving to be beneficial to the company's overall margin. To create more efficient distribution, pricing, and advertising campaigns, research should be conducted on each country's population characteristics. Additionally, research should identify any economic and political conditions that may hinder customers' willingness and ability to purchase items, specifically bikes, with more generous margins.

Therefore, marketing teams should be created for each country to focus on researching competitors and identifying the company's strengths, weaknesses, opportunities, and threats. Ideally, four teams will be created, one for each country.
